OL,3,CCalls for Channel Islands to take more
OL,4,Caction to stop young people vaping
OL,6,FIn the Channel Islands, children as
OL,7,Fyoung as 11 have been reported to be
OL,8,Fsmoking e-cigarettes.
OL,10,FIn , the number of secondary school
OL,11,Fpupils who vape regularly has risen
OL,12,Ffrom 2% in 2019 to 10% in 2022.
OL,14,FHealth officials have spoken out on
OL,15,Fthe negative impacts smoking can have
OL,16,Fon young people.
OL,18,FJersey's Director of Public Health,
OL,19,FProfessor Peter Bradley, said: "There
OL,20,Fare a number of chemicals in the
OL,21,Fvapes, which we're concerned about.
